YKrax... I can't remember exactly what I did. After I installed DaemonToolsPro using the main executable I unpacked the "loader.rar" and my virus scanner kept continuously bugging me about the 2 or 3 executable that were in the loader. I eventually decided to click on the first one, but it didn't seem to do anything. Eventually I tried them all and then eventually I put all 3 executables in the same folder where DaemonToolsPro installed. I instructed my virus scanner to ignore all 3 executables and then clicked each of them again. I knew it had worked when I loaded the Daemon Tools program and the top of the window said "Ru-Board Edition" instead of "20 days left to evaluate" or something along those lines. Sorry I can't be more specific about it all, but I'm just not sure which thing I did got it to work for me...
